arch:property.oc:show_val: Locus 24 Cistern floor and beyond the north wall of the Cistern-Reservoir.
5.90 m north south-by-4.90 m east west.

Fill extending from the South Wall-Residential Quarter Steps Locus 18 to the North Wall Locus 21. This locus is composed of former Loci 17 and 22 and Locus 16 fills, but it is finer in consistency. It is a Munsell 7.5YR 5/4 or Brown soil with pottery and stones.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
